&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;OXFORD CENTRE FOR ENABLEMENT&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;BAND 6 Physiotherapist in Spasticity Clinic&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;15 hours per week. 12 months maternity leave cover.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking to recruit an enthusiastic physiotherapist to work in the multidisciplinary spasticity clinic at the Oxford Centre for Enablement.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Oxford Centre for Enablement (OCE) is a level one specialist neurological rehabilitation centre providing assessment, management and treatment for patients with a wide range of neurological disorders. This post will be based in the outpatient Spasticity Clinic. The role will include assessment of spasticity and its impact on a patient’s function, identification of appropriate goals, advice on physical management and splinting as well as supporting a botulinum toxin injector to deliver safe and effective interventions. This is a very supportive clinical environment and the post holder can expect to develop their knowledge and skills within a well-established and experienced team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You are strongly encouraged to discuss the post in advance of applying.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing date 9-Nov-2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Brid Spillane&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Clinical Specialist Physiotherapist&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
